      ],
      "studyNotes": "A single cantabile melody floats over an unbroken stream of sextuplet arpeggios for nearly six minutes. Follow the top voice against the bass line: the middle texture never stops moving, yet the piece reads as three slow layers. Written in 1827, published posthumously in 1857 (transposed to G major by the first publisher; the original G-flat is what you hear)."
    },
