      ],
      "studyNotes": "Right-hand scale ribbons run almost without pause — E-flat major spun into continuous triplet eighths — until a stormy B minor middle section snaps the mood. Watch the left hand: a plain waltz-like accompaniment that keeps the racing right hand honest, and a coda that ends the major-key piece defiantly in minor."
