      ],
      "studyNotes": "Cascading sixteenth-note arpeggios open in A-flat minor even though the piece is titled in the major — the sunrise into A-flat major arrives only after each cascade resolves. The trio section is a long-breathed chorale in C-sharp minor. Listen for the left hand's offbeat chords answering every right-hand fall."
